'''ABC Kimberley''' is an [[ABC Local Radio]] station based in [[Broome, Western Australia]], owned by the [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]]. Its callsign is '''6BE''' and the station transmits on [[AM broadcasting|AM]].
==History==
ABC Kimberley began broadcasting from Broome on 26 January 1990, with a staff of one. Since then the station continued an expansion program that now sees broadcasting of some 30 hours of radio each week.
